cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with pruning algorithms for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses theoretical analysis of the generalization error of DNNs, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
